dsDescriptionValue.value:
This unit ran weekly during sessions 10-20 of CAPS/88. It asked Rs to report whether or not they had engaged in any of the following activities during the last 7 days: skipped classes, attended religious services, attended a sporting event, gone to a concert, gone to a movie, gone to a party, had a date, visited their hometown.

Next, Rs were asked whether they had experienced a major event (good or bad) during the past 7 days. If so, they were given 3 lines to describe the event.

Using a 5 point like/dislike scale, Rs rated how much they would like to engage in each of 15 activities (plus any activities they had filled in in previous weeks in response to 'other').

For a specified time of day (morning,afternoon, or evening), R was asked to recall what he/she was doing the previous day. R chose from a specified list of activities and could indicate and fill in 'other'. Thinking about that period of time, Rs rated how well a number of adjectives described them.

The unit was developed by Dr. Lou Penner to be used as a measure of attitudinal and behavioral consistency. An identical unit was run in sessions 7-16 of CAPS/86.
